# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: BattleOfRahayal
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah turned up and saw a great rift tear through the heavens."
    new "Sarah turned up and saw a great rift tear through the heavens."

    old "She could not recall how she had come here."
    new "She could not recall how she had come here."

    old "How much time had passed, between the Black Pyramid and this moment."
    new "How much time had passed, between the Black Pyramid and this moment."

    old "All she knew..."
    new "All she knew..."

    old "Was that she was ready."
    new "Was that she was ready."

    old "The endless hordes of inky fiends crawled and flew and dragged themselves towards the city."
    new "The endless hordes of inky fiends crawled and flew and dragged themselves towards the city."

    old "Just as before in Lethram, she saw no two creatures perfectly the same."
    new "Just as before in Lethram, she saw no two creatures perfectly the same."

    old "Each some random abstract variation."
    new "Each some random abstract variation."

    old "Only their pale masks were the same."
    new "Only their pale masks were the same."

    old "Hollow and cold."
    new "Hollow and cold."

    old "For this was what these creatures were."
    new "For this was what these creatures were."

    old "They were not filled with rage, or hatred or any beliefs that could be opposed."
    new "They were not filled with rage, or hatred or any beliefs that could be opposed."

    old "They simply devoured and tore apart life."
    new "They simply devoured and tore apart life."

    old "Like forces of nature, huricans and earthquakes. Calamities that struck without motive."
    new "Like forces of nature, huricans and earthquakes. Calamities that struck without motive."

    old "Sarah wondered if it was worse that these creatures did what they did, with no hatred or malice to drive them."
    new "Sarah wondered if it was worse that these creatures did what they did, with no hatred or malice to drive them."

    old "As the first wave of the beasts rushed across the city's defenses, they landed in the still busy squares."
    new "As the first wave of the beasts rushed across the city's defenses, they landed in the still busy squares."

    old "Just as in Lethram, the people had barely realized what was happening, before the horror was upon them."
    new "Just as in Lethram, the people had barely realized what was happening, before the horror was upon them."

    old "Their walls and fortresses and armies had been build to resist enemies that they understood."
    new "Their walls and fortresses and armies had been build to resist enemies that they understood."

    old "Not creatures like these."
    new "Not creatures like these."

    old "Sarah watched as one of the creatures landed in a busy market square."
    new "Sarah watched as one of the creatures landed in a busy market square."

    old "For a moment, the people simply looked on, stunned."
    new "For a moment, the people simply looked on, stunned."

    old "And perhaps the creature itself was frozen for a moment, confused by how easy it all was."
    new "And perhaps the creature itself was frozen for a moment, confused by how easy it all was."

    old "Then, its inky body morphed into a sharp tendril and shot forward, impaling the nearest unlucky soul."
    new "Then, its inky body morphed into a sharp tendril and shot forward, impaling the nearest unlucky soul."

    old "The tendril found no resistance as it punctured the body, impaling it."
    new "The tendril found no resistance as it punctured the body, impaling it."

    old "The voidling lifted up the corpse, studying it out of some alien interest."
    new "The voidling lifted up the corpse, studying it out of some alien interest."

    old "Then, more followed."
    new "Then, more followed."

    old "Raining down from the sky, hundreds at a time, the fiendish beasts emerged from their purple fog."
    new "Raining down from the sky, hundreds at a time, the fiendish beasts emerged from their purple fog."

    old "All across the city, the carnage began."
    new "All across the city, the carnage began."

    old "They had not expected this enemy. But they had also not expected that an attack could happen everywhere all at once."
    new "They had not expected this enemy. But they had also not expected that an attack could happen everywhere all at once."

    old "The entire city erupted into violence, all at once."
    new "The entire city erupted into violence, all at once."

    old "Sarah could hear the growing chorus of screams."
    new "Sarah could hear the growing chorus of screams."

    old "Who was she, but one girl..."
    new "Who was she, but one girl..."

    old "How could she or anyone hope to stop this onslaught?"
    new "How could she or anyone hope to stop this onslaught?"

    old "In some of the squares, Sarah could see the city's regimented legions begin to moblize."
    new "In some of the squares, Sarah could see the city's regimented legions begin to moblize."

    old "The Empire had the greatest armies on the earth, but they had been trained to defeat other armies, not these creatures."
    new "The Empire had the greatest armies on the earth, but they had been trained to defeat other armies, not these creatures."

    old "She saw small groups of men, brave as they were, charge forward in disciplined formations."
    new "She saw small groups of men, brave as they were, charge forward in disciplined formations."

    old "The void beasts swung at them, cleaving some in half with no effort at all."
    new "The void beasts swung at them, cleaving some in half with no effort at all."

    old "The strength of these void beasts was unlike anything else."
    new "The strength of these void beasts was unlike anything else."

    old "And the shapes and angles of their body made attack difficult."
    new "And the shapes and angles of their body made attack difficult."

    old "Sarah watched as one legion soldier swung his blade, stabbing at the inky body, only for the body to shape and twist away."
    new "Sarah watched as one legion soldier swung his blade, stabbing at the inky body, only for the body to shape and twist away."

    old "The creature seized the brave soldier and ripped its head off."
    new "The creature seized the brave soldier and ripped its head off."

    old "The body fell motionless to the ground."
    new "The body fell motionless to the ground."

    old "Despite this, more soldiers charged."
    new "Despite this, more soldiers charged."

    old "Bit by bit, slashing their blades, stabbing their spears, they managed to rip and tear at the inky body of the Voidling."
    new "Bit by bit, slashing their blades, stabbing their spears, they managed to rip and tear at the inky body of the Voidling."

    old "With a high pitched scream, the beast collapsed to the ground."
    new "With a high pitched scream, the beast collapsed to the ground."

    old "They were strong, but not beyond killing."
    new "They were strong, but not beyond killing."

    old "But for every voidling they brought down, many more soldier were killed."
    new "But for every voidling they brought down, many more soldier were killed."

    old "Watching the carnage unfold, Sarah could not help but feel repulsed at her own inaction."
    new "Watching the carnage unfold, Sarah could not help but feel repulsed at her own inaction."

    old "She wanted desperately to save these people."
    new "She wanted desperately to save these people."

    old "But she had promised the Order to hold off."
    new "But she had promised the Order to hold off."

    old "To wait until the creatures had broken through the Black Pyramid."
    new "To wait until the creatures had broken through the Black Pyramid."

    old "Helplessly, she watched on as the carnage continued."
    new "Helplessly, she watched on as the carnage continued."

    old "Until finally, she heard the signal."
    new "Until finally, she heard the signal."

    old "Somewhere in the city, one of the founders had blown a horn, its heavy droning sound calling out across the city."
    new "Somewhere in the city, one of the founders had blown a horn, its heavy droning sound calling out across the city."

    old "And all at once, all the mages emerged."
    new "And all at once, all the mages emerged."

    old "The voidling army had entered the city, but it would now prove a trap."
    new "The voidling army had entered the city, but it would now prove a trap."

    old "Sarah leapt from the top of the roof, using her magic to keep herself from falling."
    new "Sarah leapt from the top of the roof, using her magic to keep herself from falling."

    old "She painted the markings of her spell with her hands, moving fast and on memory alone."
    new "She painted the markings of her spell with her hands, moving fast and on memory alone."

    old "She drew on the energy around her, channeling it through the focus, and speaking the words."
    new "She drew on the energy around her, channeling it through the focus, and speaking the words."

    old "All as Xan had once taught her, which by now, was second nature to her."
    new "All as Xan had once taught her, which by now, was second nature to her."

    old "Magical pale fire rushed out, meeting the first Voidling she saw."
    new "Magical pale fire rushed out, meeting the first Voidling she saw."

    old "The creature only saw her when it was too late."
    new "The creature only saw her when it was too late."

    old "Blue fire rained down on it, catching its inky body."
    new "Blue fire rained down on it, catching its inky body."

    old "A high pitched hissing scream emerged as it fell to the earth, writing in pain."
    new "A high pitched hissing scream emerged as it fell to the earth, writing in pain."

    old "But it could do nothing to stop the flame."
    new "But it could do nothing to stop the flame."

    old "Regular weapons were weak against the voidlings, but magic was their weakness."
    new "Regular weapons were weak against the voidlings, but magic was their weakness."

    old "The flame did not just harm them, it caught their inky blood on fire, as if it were no different than oil."
    new "The flame did not just harm them, it caught their inky blood on fire, as if it were no different than oil."

    old "Still, as the beast died screaming, its pale mask remained unchanged."
    new "Still, as the beast died screaming, its pale mask remained unchanged."

    old "Alive. Dying. Dead."
    new "Alive. Dying. Dead."

    old "It didn't matter. Always that same unmoving expression."
    new "It didn't matter. Always that same unmoving expression."

    old "The fires rushed along its body, turning its body to ashes."
    new "The fires rushed along its body, turning its body to ashes."

    old "The purple mist around them, which they seemed to live and thrive in, also caught fire and receded."
    new "The purple mist around them, which they seemed to live and thrive in, also caught fire and receded."

    old "Before the magic, they were powerless."
    new "Before the magic, they were powerless."

    old "From a distance, Sarah saw Samayra jumping in between a group of citizens and a void beast."
    new "From a distance, Sarah saw Samayra jumping in between a group of citizens and a void beast."

    old "The creature advanced rapidly, half dragging and clawing its way forward."
    new "The creature advanced rapidly, half dragging and clawing its way forward."

    old "Just as it neared them, Samayra released a surge of flame."
    new "Just as it neared them, Samayra released a surge of flame."

    old "The fires rose up like a wall, blocking off the creatures advance."
    new "The fires rose up like a wall, blocking off the creatures advance."

    old "Parts of the void beast burned away as it stopped."
    new "Parts of the void beast burned away as it stopped."

    old "For a moment, it stood still, reconsidering its decision to think of the girl as easy prey."
    new "For a moment, it stood still, reconsidering its decision to think of the girl as easy prey."

    old "Then, slowly, it began to back away, crawling into a different direction."
    new "Then, slowly, it began to back away, crawling into a different direction."

    old "Sarah sighed a breath of relief as she saw Samayra comfort the citizens and lead them further to safety."
    new "Sarah sighed a breath of relief as she saw Samayra comfort the citizens and lead them further to safety."

    old "She wanted to be with her, even though she knew she could not."
    new "She wanted to be with her, even though she knew she could not."

    old "Gods...she thought to herself."
    new "Gods...she thought to herself."

    old "Keep her safe."
    new "Keep her safe."

    old "In the distance, Sarah saw more mages."
    new "In the distance, Sarah saw more mages."

    old "Emerged from their hiding, they unleashed all the pent up power unto the fiends."
    new "Emerged from their hiding, they unleashed all the pent up power unto the fiends."

    old "Fire reigned through the streets, eagerly searching out more voidlings."
    new "Fire reigned through the streets, eagerly searching out more voidlings."

    old "The screams of the citizens of Rahayal were now mixed with the hissing screams of the Void creatures."
    new "The screams of the citizens of Rahayal were now mixed with the hissing screams of the Void creatures."

    old "The battle was turning."
    new "The battle was turning."

    old "Near her, Sarah saw a pair of mages casting binding wards on one of the voidlings."
    new "Near her, Sarah saw a pair of mages casting binding wards on one of the voidlings."

    old "The creature raged and screamed as it bashed itself against its new prison."
    new "The creature raged and screamed as it bashed itself against its new prison."

    old "They would die."
    new "They would die."

    old "But for some, a worse fate, she thought."
    new "But for some, a worse fate, she thought."

    old "It was hard to feel sympathy for the creatures, but caught in a trap, they seemed almost animal like."
    new "It was hard to feel sympathy for the creatures, but caught in a trap, they seemed almost animal like."

    old "Then, suddenly, all the world shook and trembled."
    new "Then, suddenly, all the world shook and trembled."

    old "Sarah felt her own legs give out from under her as the earth rocked back and forth."
    new "Sarah felt her own legs give out from under her as the earth rocked back and forth."

    old "She turned towards the source of thunderous noise and saw chunks of earth, the size of houses, flying through the air."
    new "She turned towards the source of thunderous noise and saw chunks of earth, the size of houses, flying through the air."

    old "Where before there had been a large building, a temple of some kind, now she could only see a black pillar."
    new "Where before there had been a large building, a temple of some kind, now she could only see a black pillar."

    old "No, she thought, realizing what she was actually seeing."
    new "No, she thought, realizing what she was actually seeing."

    old "Not a pillar."
    new "Not a pillar."

    old "A horn."
    new "A horn."

    old "As the ink black horn ripped apart the earth, out burrowed a beast even larger than any building."
    new "As the ink black horn ripped apart the earth, out burrowed a beast even larger than any building."

    old "Breaking through the surface of the earth, the creature violently emerged, casting of rocks as it shook free."
    new "Breaking through the surface of the earth, the creature violently emerged, casting of rocks as it shook free."

    old "All around them, the stones rained down, tearing apart buildings and bodies."
    new "All around them, the stones rained down, tearing apart buildings and bodies."

    old "Sarah trembled at the sight of a beast the size of a mountain."
    new "Sarah trembled at the sight of a beast the size of a mountain."

    old "The voidlings came in many shapes and forms, but she had never seen anything like this."
    new "The voidlings came in many shapes and forms, but she had never seen anything like this."

    old "As it brought down one claw, it ripped apart another building."
    new "As it brought down one claw, it ripped apart another building."

    old "Left free, the beast might tear the greatest city on earth down in a matter of hours."
    new "Left free, the beast might tear the greatest city on earth down in a matter of hours."

    old "Sarah felt the purple mist strengthen again, rushing around her, poluting the very air."
    new "Sarah felt the purple mist strengthen again, rushing around her, poluting the very air."

    old "Toxic spores she did not dare to breathe."
    new "Toxic spores she did not dare to breathe."

    old "She focussed, pushing away all the carnage, destruction and screams."
    new "She focussed, pushing away all the carnage, destruction and screams."

    old "Until only clarity remained."
    new "Until only clarity remained."

    old "The voice or her own voice, clearing away all else."
    new "The voice or her own voice, clearing away all else."

    old "The vibrations in her veins. The pulsing blood."
    new "The vibrations in her veins. The pulsing blood."

    old "A power unlike any she had ever known before."
    new "A power unlike any she had ever known before."

    old "So much of it, she could hardly keep it within her."
    new "So much of it, she could hardly keep it within her."

    old "Even now, she felt the raging energy inside of her, spilling out."
    new "Even now, she felt the raging energy inside of her, spilling out."

    old "She leapt up with such ease, she felt as if she were flying."
    new "She leapt up with such ease, she felt as if she were flying."

    old "Twisting her arms and hands, she pulled in the magical energies around her."
    new "Twisting her arms and hands, she pulled in the magical energies around her."

    old "But where before there was effort, now the world obeyed her without resistance."
    new "But where before there was effort, now the world obeyed her without resistance."

    old "Torrents of magic, surged from around the whole of the city, bending around her focus."
    new "Torrents of magic, surged from around the whole of the city, bending around her focus."

    old "Then, with that same ease, she released the energy."
    new "Then, with that same ease, she released the energy."

    old "Bright red spikes of magic, cut through the behemoth."
    new "Bright red spikes of magic, cut through the behemoth."

    old "The creature roared out in pain, sending out waves of sound powerful enough to rattle stone walls."
    new "The creature roared out in pain, sending out waves of sound powerful enough to rattle stone walls."

    old "Stumbling backwards, it tried to find its balance."
    new "Stumbling backwards, it tried to find its balance."

    old "But Sarah advanced, throwing out more spikes, cutting the creature apart piece by piece."
    new "But Sarah advanced, throwing out more spikes, cutting the creature apart piece by piece."

    old "As she turned her hand and released more punishment, she wondered at just how easy it all felt."
    new "As she turned her hand and released more punishment, she wondered at just how easy it all felt."

    old "The pulsing blood in her veins, sharpening her mind, in tune to the magical energies around her."
    new "The pulsing blood in her veins, sharpening her mind, in tune to the magical energies around her."

    old "Another spike cut through the behemoth's leg, causing it to stumble towards the earth."
    new "Another spike cut through the behemoth's leg, causing it to stumble towards the earth."

    old "She did not let up."
    new "She did not let up."

    old "Each spike drove further into the beast, ripping parts of it off."
    new "Each spike drove further into the beast, ripping parts of it off."

    old "It's inky body, flowing out into the streets, poluting the earth."
    new "It's inky body, flowing out into the streets, poluting the earth."

    old "But slowly, its breathing stopped."
    new "But slowly, its breathing stopped."

    old "Sarah hovered over the massive carcass."
    new "Sarah hovered over the massive carcass."

    old "The greatest beast she had ever seen. And with the aid of the Betrayer God, she had unmade it with such ease."
    new "The greatest beast she had ever seen. And with the aid of the Betrayer God, she had unmade it with such ease."

    old "How many lives had she saved in killing this thing?"
    new "How many lives had she saved in killing this thing?"

    old "Had it all been worth it?"
    new "Had it all been worth it?"

    old "For a moment, she could believe."
    new "For a moment, she could believe."

    old "Sarah watched as the other mages advanced on the creature, flanking it from every side."
    new "Sarah watched as the other mages advanced on the creature, flanking it from every side."

    old "They began to throw their magics at it, whipping the beast into a furious frenzy."
    new "They began to throw their magics at it, whipping the beast into a furious frenzy."

    old "It roared, sending out shockwaves of sound that rattled the stone foundations."
    new "It roared, sending out shockwaves of sound that rattled the stone foundations."

    old "It swept with its great claws, tearing apart the earth, taking out entire buildings."
    new "It swept with its great claws, tearing apart the earth, taking out entire buildings."

    old "But the mages still advanced."
    new "But the mages still advanced."

    old "Leaping out, Sarah joined in, throwing her own magical fire onto the beast."
    new "Leaping out, Sarah joined in, throwing her own magical fire onto the beast."

    old "The behemoth continued to scream, roar and rage as the magical flames rushed up along its body."
    new "The behemoth continued to scream, roar and rage as the magical flames rushed up along its body."

    old "But the other mages in the Order did not give it any reprieve."
    new "But the other mages in the Order did not give it any reprieve."

    old "Dozens, Sarah could count."
    new "Dozens, Sarah could count."

    old "Dozens of mages all together, raining down their power on this one beast."
    new "Dozens of mages all together, raining down their power on this one beast."

    old "And she stood in awe of their combined power."
    new "And she stood in awe of their combined power."

    old "For a moment, she was glad."
    new "For a moment, she was glad."

    old "Glad in knowing that she had their support, regardless of their demand."
    new "Glad in knowing that she had their support, regardless of their demand."

    old "For without them, she would have been powerless to stop a beast of this size."
    new "For without them, she would have been powerless to stop a beast of this size."

    old "The behemoth let out a final roar as it collapsed to the earth."
    new "The behemoth let out a final roar as it collapsed to the earth."

    old "As the great beast fell, its body began to untangle itself from whatever held it together."
    new "As the great beast fell, its body began to untangle itself from whatever held it together."

    old "Sarah watched as great plumes of purple smoke, toxix spores, filled the air."
    new "Sarah watched as great plumes of purple smoke, toxix spores, filled the air."

    old "So great was the miasma, that everywhere it landed, wild and alien plants quickly sprouted and grew."
    new "So great was the miasma, that everywhere it landed, wild and alien plants quickly sprouted and grew."

    old "A twisted nature overtook the ruined streets of Rahayal."
    new "A twisted nature overtook the ruined streets of Rahayal."

    old "Sarah stumbled about, so heavy and thick the fog, she could hardly make out the sky."
    new "Sarah stumbled about, so heavy and thick the fog, she could hardly make out the sky."

    old "Was this what their world looked like, she wondered to herself?"
    new "Was this what their world looked like, she wondered to herself?"

    old "Did these strange plants appear to them as natural and normal as those of her own world?"
    new "Did these strange plants appear to them as natural and normal as those of her own world?"

    old "She stumbled on, around her, more sounds of battle, though slowly fading."
    new "She stumbled on, around her, more sounds of battle, though slowly fading."

    old "A great force pulled her forward."
    new "A great force pulled her forward."

    old "Something near her."
    new "Something near her."

    old "She came upon a clearing, a small huddled mess of ink, near the center of it."
    new "She came upon a clearing, a small huddled mess of ink, near the center of it."

    old "Sarah stood still and watched."
    new "Sarah stood still and watched."

    old "Slowly, it began to move."
    new "Slowly, it began to move."

    old "Only its head."
    new "Only its head."

    old "The rest of it, ripped and mangled, torn and wounded."
    new "The rest of it, ripped and mangled, torn and wounded."

    old "Near the edges of its form, its inky body was disolving."
    new "Near the edges of its form, its inky body was disolving."

    old "The pale mask turned, as if observing her."
    new "The pale mask turned, as if observing her."

    old "It uttered out a word in broken speech."
    new "It uttered out a word in broken speech."

    old "It seemed to require all its power just to utter these few words."
    new "It seemed to require all its power just to utter these few words."

    old "Death was near for it, she knew that much."
    new "Death was near for it, she knew that much."

    old "Why? You attacked first...what were we supposed to do?"
    new "Why? You attacked first...what were we supposed to do?"

    old "The creature nodded with its mask."
    new "The creature nodded with its mask."

    old "This...pain..."
    new "This...pain..."

    old "End...it..."
    new "End...it..."

    old "Sarah felt only pity for it, despite everything."
    new "Sarah felt only pity for it, despite everything."

    old "She raised her hand and violently focussed the magical energies around the creature."
    new "She raised her hand and violently focussed the magical energies around the creature."

    old "A torrent of fire erupted around the beast, evaporting it in a near instant."
    new "A torrent of fire erupted around the beast, evaporting it in a near instant."

    old "She had come to stop them. Kill them."
    new "She had come to stop them. Kill them."

    old "But this hardly felt like a battle. This felt like the end of something."
    new "But this hardly felt like a battle. This felt like the end of something."

    old "The creature let out a brief hiss as it burned, though it seemed glad for it."
    new "The creature let out a brief hiss as it burned, though it seemed glad for it."

    old "Glad for it to be over."
    new "Glad for it to be over."

    old "Only ashes remained where the creature had stood."
    new "Only ashes remained where the creature had stood."

    old "Sarah wandered away."
    new "Sarah wandered away."

    old "The sounds of battle began to die out."
    new "The sounds of battle began to die out."

    old "She burned away the alien plants where she could find them, but the voidlings grew ever more sparse."
    new "She burned away the alien plants where she could find them, but the voidlings grew ever more sparse."

    old "Slowly, the sky above her began to clear."
    new "Slowly, the sky above her began to clear."

    old "Sarah stumbled through the ruined street of Rahayal for a while longer, trying to save those that she still could."
    new "Sarah stumbled through the ruined street of Rahayal for a while longer, trying to save those that she still could."

    old "Most were beyond saving."
    new "Most were beyond saving."

    old "It took a long time before she finally made her way to one of the nearby towers."
    new "It took a long time before she finally made her way to one of the nearby towers."

    old "The thing stood only partially, but sound enough to risk the climb."
    new "The thing stood only partially, but sound enough to risk the climb."

    old "As she reached the top, the sky had cleared and Sarah could look out over the city."
    new "As she reached the top, the sky had cleared and Sarah could look out over the city."

    old "Or what remained of it."
    new "Or what remained of it."

    old "The greatest city in the world, the greatest Empire, brought to ruin."
    new "The greatest city in the world, the greatest Empire, brought to ruin."

    old "But in the midsts of all that destruction, she saw people."
    new "But in the midsts of all that destruction, she saw people."

    old "From this height, like ants, but they survived."
    new "From this height, like ants, but they survived."

    old "Small crowds of citizens, soldiers, working together to recover from the calamity that had just taken place."
    new "Small crowds of citizens, soldiers, working together to recover from the calamity that had just taken place."

    old "She doubted many would even properly understand what they had been witness to."
    new "She doubted many would even properly understand what they had been witness to."

    old "The last of the purple miasma began to pull back, evaporate, as if it could not persist in this world without the voidlings."
    new "The last of the purple miasma began to pull back, evaporate, as if it could not persist in this world without the voidlings."

    old "The damage was great."
    new "The damage was great."

    old "But they would survive."
    new "But they would survive."

    old "More importantly, she realized what she was not seeing."
    new "More importantly, she realized what she was not seeing."

    old "The voidlings."
    new "The voidlings."

    old "Driven off or perhaps even destroyed."
    new "Driven off or perhaps even destroyed."

    old "Whatever the outcome, they were gone from the city."
    new "Whatever the outcome, they were gone from the city."

    old "They had won."
    new "They had won."

    old "For now, she realized."
    new "For now, she realized."

    old "She steeled her resolve as she looked out over the ruins."
    new "She steeled her resolve as she looked out over the ruins."

    old "This was a battle in the war."
    new "This was a battle in the war."

    old "Unlike Lethram, this city would live. Survive."
    new "Unlike Lethram, this city would live. Survive."

    old "But in what state?"
    new "But in what state?"

